li><strong>For Physical Therapy:</strong> If appropriate for simple commands, create written step-by-step instructions with accompanying pictures (e.g., \"Walk to the [picture of mat] Mat\").</li>\n            </ul>\n        </li>\n        <li><strong>Multi-Sensory Approach and Reduced Auditory Reliance:</strong>\n            <ul>\n                <li>Always pair spoken instructions with visual aids or physical demonstrations. Minimize solely auditory tasks.</li>\n                <li>Ensure learning environments are rich with textures, manipulatives, and opportunities for touch and exploration.</li>\n                <li>Allow for frequent movement breaks and incorporate fidget tools if helpful for concentration.</li>\n            </ul>\n        </li>\n    </ul>\n\n    <p>\n        Lam Ah Li presents with significant developmental delays, particularly in physical and social-emotional domains, alongside concerns in language. However, the child\'s strong Kinesthetic, Reading/Writing, and Visual learning styles offer powerful avenues for intervention. A comprehensive and integrated approach, heavily relying on hands-on activities, clear visual aids, and incorporating early literacy elements, will be most effective in supporting Lam Ah Li\'s development across all identified areas, helping to bridge developmental gaps and foster engagement and progress.\n    </p>\n</div>', '2025-11-19 04:37:00', '2025-11-30 14:29:20'),
